SUCCESS STORY


Insight
Innovation
Impact

Using MealSense™ to drive student participation makes sense
 

INSIGHT
INNOVATION
IMPACT




Insight

                                    One of the challenges schools face in increasing free and reduced meal program participation is that many eligible parents often do not submit applications due to lack of awareness about the program, misunderstanding of eligibility qualifications, lack of time and the stigma associated with receiving free meals.
                                

See our innovation




Innovation

                                    Our proprietary MealSense™ program is a step-by-step process to increase free and reduced-price applications. Meal Sense delivers integrated communication solutions to raise program awareness and keep it “top-of-mind” for parents, while providing clear, simple and easily accessible applications and information.
                                

See our impact




Impact

                                    Districts that implemented the Aramark MealSense™ Program experienced a 10% to 25% increase in free and reduced applications. This means more students are receiving nutritious meals in order to perform their best throughout the day and districts are maximizing their federal reimbursements for school meal programs.
                                

CONTACT US














Patrick Sandoval, Chef/Area Supervisor
Pflugerville Independent School District, Pflugerville, TX



Employee Spotlight



                            "What I hope kids take away from [our nutrition education program] is that food is ever-changing, and food is extremely exciting, and there’s such a vast array of different food out there. Healthy foods can be fun, exciting and taste good."

                        





Walter Doughty, Dir. of Nutrition and Transportation
Waukegan Public School District, Waukegan, IL



Partner Focus



                            "Aramark has been great in their presentation of meal planning and providing the menus for us within USDA nutritional guidelines. There’s a constant chance to make sure that everything is new and different, and that they meet those guidelines that most of us wouldn’t be able to."
                        










